### What problem does this feature solve?
Hi, 

in a mixin I have specified:
```
props: {
  value: {
    type: String,
    default: '',
  },
}
```

Then, in my component, I have tried to override it:
```
props: {
  value: {
    type: Boolean,
    default: false,
  },
}
```

However, that results in an error: `Invalid prop: type check failed for prop "value". Expected String, got Boolean.`

Is this a bug, and if not, do you think it would be a useful feature?

Thanks. I have a case when 90% of my components take a string value, but some need an override (different text inputs all take a string value, but checkboxes are true/false).

